\begin_layout Subsection
Estimation of Bad Debts
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are two methods:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Percentage of sales (the sales revenue approach)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Multiply the sales by some predetermined percentage and find out the bad
 debt exesnse.
 It can be thinked of as 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

creating matching on the I/S
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 This method is considered less accurate, thus accounting rules tend to
 avoid it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Aging of A/R or percentage of the A/R (the gross A/R approach)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Multiply the ending A/R by some predetermined percentage and find out the
 allowance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order to provide more accurate estimate, it makes sense to not treat
 all receivables in the same manner, but rather use an 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
